duction to UIC Library resources and services.    The library's collection of Research Guides provide streamlined access to discipline specific databases, books, articles and more for study and research. Course Guides provide access to course-specific resources and information.  The Nursing Research and Subject Guide is your portal to resources and information for nursing research and clinical practice.  The Library Toolbox (left) provides quick access to resources and services that you might frequently use. Seperate links to these also appear throughout the library's Web site and Research Guides.  Nursing Library Liaisons (right) provides the contact information for librarians at each campus location. In addition to phone numbers and email, users can also Chat with a Librarian (IM) from 8 a.m.-1:00 a.m.                 Library Toolbox     Find books and more by searching the library catalog:  Keyword Title Author Subject ISBN/ISSN     Books from other Illinois libraries may be found and requested via the I-Share Catalog .   Find full text  Search for E-journals, Magazines, Newspapers or E-books  Full text for a known article  Citation Matcher   links to full text information from within library database results.   My Account  Connect to My Account in the Library Catalog   My Interlibrary Loans  UIC faculty, staff and current students can use My Interlibrary Loans to request materials that are not available through the UIC Library.   RefWorks  Create your own citation database and quickly build bibliographies with                 Nursing Library Liaisons         Chicago  Graduate Nursing  Rebecca Raszewski (312) 996-2759  raszewr1@uic.edu Skype: raszewr1  Pre-Licensure & Graduate Entry Nursing  Annie Nickum (312) 413-2464  anicku2@uic.edu  Schedule Appointment     Rockford  Cynthia Reynolds  (815) 395-5658 cmreynol@uic.edu      Peoria & Quad Cities  Emily Johnson-Barlow (309) 671-8490  lib-pref@uic.edu    Urbana & Springfield  Ryan Rafferty (217) 244-0607  lib-lhsu-